[
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm looking into migrating some libraries to the new compiler, starting with <code>roc-parser</code> and <code>unicode</code>. Most of it looks fairly straightforward, but I'm not entirely sure how to reorganize modules. For example, in <code>roc-parser</code>, the <code>Xml</code> module currently starts like this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"no\">Xml</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">XmlDeclaration</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">XmlVersion</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Node</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Attribute</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">xml_parser</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Parser</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exposing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"no\">Parser</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">const</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">skip</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">keep</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">one_or_more</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">one_of</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">many</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">between</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">alt</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">chomp_while</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">flatten</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">lazy</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">chomp_until</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">String</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exposing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">parse_str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">string</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Utf8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">digits</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">codeunit_satisfies</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"no\">Xml</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">xml_declaration</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"no\">Given</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">XmlDeclaration</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Missing</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">root</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Node</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"no\">XmlDeclaration</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">version</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">XmlVersion</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">encoding</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"no\">Given</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">XmlEncoding</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Missing</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"no\">XmlVersion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">after_dot</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">U8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">implements</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"no\">Eq</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">v1_dot0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">XmlVersion</span>\n<span class=\"n\">v1_dot0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"vi\">@XmlVersion</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"ss\">after_dot</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">},</span>\n<span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">...</span>\n<span class=\"n\">expect</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">...</span>\n<span class=\"o\">...</span>\n<span class=\"n\">xml_parser</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Parser</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Utf8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Xml</span>\n<span class=\"n\">xml_parser</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">const</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">xml_declaration</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">root</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">xml_declaration</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">root</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">},</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">keep</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p_prolog</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">keep</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p_element</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">skip</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">many</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p_whitespace</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n<span class=\"o\">...</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Should I migrate it to something like this?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Parser</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exposing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"no\">Parser</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">const</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">skip</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">keep</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">one_or_more</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">one_of</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">many</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">between</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">alt</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">chomp_while</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">flatten</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">lazy</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">chomp_until</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">String</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exposing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">parse_str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">string</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Utf8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">digits</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">codeunit_satisfies</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"no\">Xml</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">xml_declaration</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"no\">Given</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">XmlDeclaration</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Missing</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">root</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Node</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n\n<span class=\"no\">XmlDeclaration</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">version</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">XmlVersion</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">encoding</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"no\">Given</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">XmlEncoding</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Missing</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"no\">XmlVersion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">after_dot</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">U8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">is_eq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">XmlVersion</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">XmlVersion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Bool</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">is_eq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">v1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v2</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v1</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">after_dot</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">==</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v2</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">after_dot</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">v1_dot0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">XmlVersion</span>\n<span class=\"n\">v1_dot0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">after_dot</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"o\">...</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">xml_parser</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Parser</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Utf8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Xml</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">xml_parser</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">const</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">xml_declaration</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">root</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"n\">xml_declaration</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">root</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">keep</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p_prolog</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">keep</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p_element</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">skip</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">many</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p_whitespace</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">...</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">expect</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">...</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Specifically:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The main type (<code>Xml</code>) must always be defined with <code>:=</code> or <code>::</code>. In this case, I've migrated it from a type alias to a type declaration. Is that correct?</li>\n<li><code>implements [Eq]</code> no longer exists so we must implement <code>is_eq</code> manually? Or is a new syntax coming?</li>\n<li>The @XmlVersion syntax was removed, now we must rely on the type declaration, correct?</li>\n<li>A function that returns a record must double the curly brackets? e.g. <code>|root| { {xml_declaration, root } }</code></li>\n<li>Any exposed function/type/constant must be part of the main type.</li>\n<li>Since we're moving <code>XmlVersion</code> and <code>XmlDeclaration</code> inside of <code>Xml</code>, perhaps we should rename them to <code>Version</code> and <code>Declaration</code> to avoid the repetition?</li>\n<li>Alternatively, should this module be split into multiple modules?</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 605887751,
        "sender_full_name": "Aurélien Geron",
        "timestamp": 1782174244
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I can answer a couple I think</p>\n<ul>\n<li>you should only need double brackets to disambiguate a punned record with a single element. If you have two it should be ok?</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>» f = |a, b| {a, b}\nassigned `f`\n» f(1, 2)\n{ a: 1.0, b: 2.0 }\n</code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li>you need is_eq but I believe there will be a way to derive it for modules</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Personal preference</p>\n<ul>\n<li>I think it makes sense to drop the Xml prefix for nested modules, given it's already namespaced. Splitting into separate module files seems a bit too much for these imo.</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 605945111,
        "sender_full_name": "Jonathan",
        "timestamp": 1782204724
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I was also looking into migrating roc-parser but was blocked by <a href=\"https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/issues/9670\">#9670</a> last I checked. It did seem like much of it could be migrated over quite mechanically besides some cases I hit where the return type had to be decoupled from the input, e.g.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>match result {\n    # this\n    Ok({key1, key2}) =&gt; Ok({key1, key2})\n    # but not\n    Ok(_) as ok_res =&gt; ok_res\n}\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>which also seemed to affect map_ok idioms.</p>",
        "id": 605946088,
        "sender_full_name": "Jonathan",
        "timestamp": 1782205037
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You will be much faster than me and I didn't really have any major API suggestions either (besides maybe some conveniences over curried <code>const</code> arguments and <code>keep</code>/<code>apply</code> redundancy), but I'd be glad to help porting libraries needed for Exercism as well.</p>",
        "id": 605946475,
        "sender_full_name": "Jonathan",
        "timestamp": 1782205146
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I can open a draft PR for roc-parser if you'd like to track progress, but I'm conscious that this is a blocker for you and I haven't been finding much time recently.</p>",
        "id": 605949951,
        "sender_full_name": "Jonathan",
        "timestamp": 1782206164
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It looks like <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"341568\">@Jared Ramirez</span> has this fixed in <a href=\"https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/pull/9688\">https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/pull/9688</a> maybe... but that just needs updating / review</p>",
        "id": 605962080,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1782209757
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think I missed that... and I'm travelling for work for a couple of days so I probably wont be able to land that until later in the week.</p>",
        "id": 605962187,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1782209790
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"361169\">@Anton</span> would you be able to look at Jared's PR?</p>",
        "id": 605962265,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1782209820
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>thanks Anton! that's ready to go once CI finishes (usually by the time CI finishes, something else has landed the branch gets out of date, then I rebase and re-run CI, and around we go haha)</p>",
        "id": 606091663,
        "sender_full_name": "Jared Ramirez",
        "timestamp": 1782246273
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"820027\">Jonathan</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/231634-beginners/topic/How.20to.20migrate.20modules/near/605949951\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I can open a draft PR for roc-parser if you'd like to track progress, but I'm conscious that this is a blocker for you and I haven't been finding much time recently.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Oops, I just saw your message now.</p>\n<p>I've opened <a href=\"https://github.com/lukewilliamboswell/roc-parser/pull/30\">https://github.com/lukewilliamboswell/roc-parser/pull/30</a></p>",
        "id": 606174842,
        "sender_full_name": "Aurélien Geron",
        "timestamp": 1782287378
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Didn't want to leave a review comment because it felt a bit too close to personal preference <span aria-label=\"laughing\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f606\" role=\"img\" title=\"laughing\">:laughing:</span> but one difference I noticed was if in some cases reducing the curried function nesting might help communicate the intent better. For instance with <code>between</code> I find that putting the <code>const</code> selector in one line shows the dropping of the first and last parse results.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>    between = |parser, open, close| {\n        const(|_| |val| |_| val)\n            .apply(open)\n            .apply(parser)\n            .apply(close)\n    }\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Again that may just be my preference, and I'm not up to date with the evolving Roc style either.</p>",
        "id": 606214876,
        "sender_full_name": "Jonathan",
        "timestamp": 1782300147
    }
]